snippet: Terry McAuliffe, a longtime Democratic fund-raiser, won by two points after outraising Kenneth T. Cuccinelli II, the attorney general, nearly two to one.
abstract: Terry McAuliffe, longtime Democratic fund-raiser and ally of Bill and Hillary Clinton, is elected governor of Virginia; narrowly defeats state's conservative attorney general, Kenneth T Cuccinelli II;  victory confirms Virginia's evolution as state increasingly dominated politically by Democratic-leaning Washington suburbs.

byline.contributor: Dalia Sussman contributed reporting from New York.

lead_paragraph: Terry McAuliffe, a longtime Democratic fund-raiser, won by two points after outraising Kenneth T. Cuccinelli II, the attorney general, nearly two to one.

headline.main: Terry McAuliffe, Democrat, Is Elected Governor of Virginia in Tight Race
headline.print_headline: Clinton Ally Slips Past Conservative in Virginia Governor’s Race
